title: Switch from JttComponent to ServiceComponent
message:
Switch from JttComponent to ServiceComponent

JttComponent was a static field in a class to ensure that all
dependencies it provides were singletons as long as application process
exists. ServiceComponent is only a singleton within JttService class and
it is destroyed as soon as service is stopped (which should never
happen).

The only dependency that actually has to be a singleton is the Ticker.
SolarEventCalculator is a singleton for now since it must be the same
object when it is used for calculations and when it is provided the
local coordinates. This will be fixed when LocationProvider will be
introduced.

title: Start implementing ServiceComponent
message:
Start implementing ServiceComponent

Create a component attached to JttService to replace the static
"singleton" jttComponent in Jtt class. Create an interface for Ticker
and make AndroidTicker an implementation of it.

API. Rewritten using android test support library.

title: Instrumentation test for TimeChangeReceiver
message:
Instrumentation test for TimeChangeReceiver

This test actually checks that when TimeChangeReceiver is triggered, it
activates JttService and that one in turn starts AndroidTicker that
broadcasts actual result.

title: Create test for TimeChangeReceiver
message:
Create test for TimeChangeReceiver

Can't verify much until TimeChangeReceiver is rewritten to not direcly

title: JttService: separate onCreate and onStartCommand
message:
JttService: separate onCreate and onStartCommand

onCreate should be called only once and should prepare all the required
objects and register receivers. onStartCommand should not perform these
things.

There was also a leftover call from AndroidTicker to update JttStatus.
This is not needed now since JttStatus itself listens to broadcasts sent
by AndroidTicker.

title: Travis: Disable initial greeter
message:
Travis: Disable initial greeter

The widget test is failing because freshly created android emulator
shows greeter overlay on first run. This breaks the test that is
attempting to navigate the launcher menu. The solution is to disable the
greeter (called "cling") by setting the system property
'ro.test_harness' to 'true'.
